    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Gunnar Henderson** stands out as the clear offensive engine for the Austin Waves with a standout 81.88 efficiency score. Facing Houser, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment and a prime leadoff spot, making him our highest-ceiling asset. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.80) and **Marcell Ozuna** (64.98) round out the top tier, with both profiting significantly from favorable wind conditions\u2014up to 10% for **Marcell Ozuna**\u2014which helps offset the standard variance inherent in facing mid-tier arms like Bradley and Taillon. **Miguel Vargas** also earns a strong recommendation at 64.07, as his combination of a leadoff role and tailwinds maximizes his scoring floor against Cameron.\n\nThe most difficult lineup decision today involved the marginal cuts, with **Josh Jung** (57.90) just barely missing the final UTIL spot. While **Josh Jung** carried a strong projection due to the high-upside matchup against the struggling Sasaki, the optimizer favored the sheer volume of plate appearances and situational power of **Heliot Ramos** and **Kyle Tucker**. Speaking of **Kyle Tucker**, he faces a major test against deGrom; while his score of 60.76 is solid, the matchup against an elite arm poses a significant risk to his ability to contribute to our AVG category, even with wind assistance. We are navigating these high-end risks carefully to preserve our game caps, keeping **Coby Mayo** and **Nolan Schanuel** on the bench despite respectable scores, as their current lineup positioning does not offer the same efficiency metrics as our primary starters.",
